{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878238000,"sessionID":"ses_2856b7b11ffeOMPvSSfB4W9F8Y","part":{"id":"prt_d7a976e9b001v5qyjowT5eTcTL","messageID":"msg_d7a95899d001pTxHwEDIAMUsRM","sessionID":"ses_2856b7b11ffeOMPvSSfB4W9F8Y","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3b1166a137054d7d9067a46cbaa418f6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-026/design.md","content":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThis design defines the Kubernetes and AgentCube provider implementations for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The providers enable deploying, managing, and invoking AI agents on Kubernetes through two deployment strategies:\n\n1. **Standard Kubernetes** (`k8s`): Deployments + NodePort Services\n2. **AgentCube Custom Resources** (`agentcube`): AgentRuntime CRs managed by Volcano AgentCube operators\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         CLI Commands                                  │\n│  publish --provider=agentcube │ publish --provider=k8s               │\n│  invoke --provider=agentcube  │ invoke --provider=k8s                │\n│  status --provider=agentcube  │ status --provider=k8s                │\n└──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n                           ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       Runtime Layer                                   │\n│  PublishRuntime │ InvokeRuntime │ StatusRuntime                       │\n└──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n           ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n           │                               │\n           ▼                               ▼\n┌───────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────┐\n│   KubernetesProvider  │    │   AgentCubeProvider   │\n│   (Standard K8s)      │    │   (AgentRuntime CR)   │\n├───────────────────────┤    ├───────────────────────┤\n│ - Deployment          │    │ - AgentRuntime CR     │\n│ - Service (NodePort)  │    │ - CustomObjectsApi    │\n│ - AppsV1Api           │    │ - CRD validation      │\n│ - CoreV1Api           │    │                       │\n└───────────────────────┘    └───────────────────────┘\n           │                               │\n           └───────────────┬───────────────┘\n                           │\n                           ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Kubernetes Cluster                                 │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │ Standard K8s     │  │ AgentCube CRD                        │     │\n│  │ - Deployment     │  │ - AgentRuntime CR                    │     │\n│  │ - NodePort SVC   │  │ - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1a1  │     │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` - Standard K8s deployments |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` - AgentRuntime CR management |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` - Orchestrates publish flow |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` - Agent invocation logic |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` - Agent status retrieval |\n| `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | Unit tests for KubernetesProvider |\n| `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider |\n| `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Unit tests for PublishRuntime |\n| `tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` | Unit tests for InvokeRuntime |\n| `tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Unit tests for StatusRuntime |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### KubernetesProvider Class\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000       # Kubernetes NodePort minimum\n    NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767       # Kubernetes NodePort maximum\n    DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120       # Deployment readiness timeout (seconds)\n    POLL_INTERVAL = 2           # Polling interval for readiness checks\n\n    namespace: str              # Target Kubernetes namespace\n    verbose: bool               # Enable verbose logging\n    _apps_api: AppsV1Api        # Kubernetes AppsV1Api client\n    _core_api: CoreV1Api        # Kubernetes CoreV1Api client\n    _logger: logging.Logger     # Module logger\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Class\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"    # CustomResource group\n    CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"                      # CustomResource version\n    CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"                  # CustomResource plural\n    SESSION_TIMEOUT = \"15m\"                      # Default session timeout\n    MAX_SESSION_DURATION = \"8h\"                  # Default max session duration\n    DEFAULT_SECRET = \"default-secret\"            # Default imagePullSecret name\n\n    namespace: str               # Target Kubernetes namespace\n    verbose: bool                # Enable verbose logging\n    _custom_api: CustomObjectsApi  # Kubernetes CustomObjectsApi client\n    _core_api: CoreV1Api         # Kubernetes CoreV1Api client\n    _logger: logging.Logger      # Module logger\n```\n\n### PublishRuntime Class\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    verbose: bool                           # Enable verbose logging\n    provider: str                            # Provider type (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n    _metadata_service: MetadataService      # Metadata management service\n    _docker_service: DockerService          # Docker operations service\n    _k8s_provider: KubernetesProvider       # Lazy-loaded for k8s provider\n    _agentcube_provider: AgentCubeProvider  # Lazy-loaded for agentcube provider\n    _logger: logging.Logger                 # Module logger\n```\n\n### InvokeRuntime Class\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    verbose: bool                           # Enable verbose logging\n    provider: str                            # Provider type (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n    _metadata_service: MetadataService      # Metadata management service\n    _k8s_provider: KubernetesProvider       # Lazy-loaded for k8s provider\n    _agentcube_provider: AgentCubeProvider  # Lazy-loaded for agentcube provider\n    _logger: logging.Logger                 # Module logger\n```\n\n### StatusRuntime Class\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    verbose: bool                           # Enable verbose logging\n    provider: str                            # Provider type (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n    _metadata_service: MetadataService      # Metadata management service\n    _k8s_provider: KubernetesProvider       # Lazy-loaded for k8s provider\n    _agentcube_provider: AgentCubeProvider  # Lazy-loaded for agentcube provider\n    _logger: logging.Logger                 # Module logger\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### KubernetesProvider Interface\n\n#### `__init__`\n\n```python\ndef __init__(\n    self,\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> None\n```\n\n- **namespace**: Target namespace for deployments\n- **verbose**: Enable debug logging\n- **kubeconfig**: Custom kubeconfig path (falls back to incluster config)\n\n#### `deploy_agent`\n\n```python\ndef deploy_agent(\n    self,\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    replicas: int = 1,\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: `{\"deployment_name\", \"service_name\", \"node_port\", \"service_url\", \"replicas\"}`\n- **Behavior**: Creates/patches Deployment and NodePort Service, waits for readiness\n\n#### `wait_for_deployment_ready`\n\n```python\ndef wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None\n```\n\n- **Raises**: `TimeoutError` if deployment not ready within timeout\n\n#### `get_agent_status`\n\n```python\ndef get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: `{\"deployment\": {...}, \"service\": {...}}`\n\n#### `delete_agent`\n\n```python\ndef delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: `{\"deployment_deleted\": bool, \"service_deleted\": bool}`\n- **Behavior**: Ignores 404 errors (resource already deleted)\n\n#### `_sanitize_name`\n\n```python\ndef _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str\n```\n\n- **Behavior**: Lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`, truncate to 63 chars, strip leading/trailing dashes\n- **Returns**: `\"default\"` if empty result\n\n---\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Interface\n\n#### `__init__`\n\n```python\ndef __init__(\n    self,\n    namespace: str = \"default\",\n    verbose: bool = False,\n    kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> None\n```\n\n#### `deploy_agent_runtime`\n\n```python\ndef deploy_agent_runtime(\n    self,\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: `{\"deployment_name\", \"agent_id\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"status\"}`\n- **CR Spec**: Sets `sessionTimeout=\"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration=\"8h\"`, `imagePullSecrets=[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n- **Readiness Probe**: Default path `/health`, default port matches `port` argument\n\n#### `get_agent_runtime`\n\n```python\ndef get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: Optional[str] = None) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: Full CR object or `None` if not found\n\n#### `delete_agent_runtime`\n\n```python\ndef delete_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: `{\"deleted\": bool, \"name\": str}` or `{\"deleted\": False, \"reason\": \"not_found\"}`\n\n---\n\n### PublishRuntime Interface\n\n#### `publish`\n\n```python\ndef publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Options**: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `namespace`, `node_port`, `replicas`\n- **Returns**: `{\"agent_name\", \"agent_id\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"deployment_type\", \"namespace\", \"k8s_deployment\", \"status\"}`\n- **Behavior**: Validates prerequisites, prepares image, deploys to K8s, updates metadata\n\n#### `_validate_publish_prerequisites`\n\n```python\ndef _validate_publish_prerequisites(\n    self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]\n) -> None\n```\n\n- **Raises**: `ValueError` for missing required fields, `RuntimeError` for Docker unavailable\n\n---\n\n### InvokeRuntime Interface\n\n#### `invoke`\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Any\n```\n\n- **Returns**: `{\"status_code\", \"response\", \"endpoint\", \"session_id\"}` (session_id if present in response headers)\n- **Behavior**: Rewrites endpoint for AgentRuntime CR to `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/`\n\n---\n\n### StatusRuntime Interface\n\n#### `get_status`\n\n```python\ndef get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n- **Returns**: Status dict with keys depending on deployment type:\n  - `not_published`: `{\"status\", \"agent_name\", \"message\"}`\n  - `AgentRuntime`: `{\"status\", \"agent_name\", \"agent_id\", \"deployment_type\", \"namespace\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"cr_status\"}`\n  - `Deployment`: `{\"status\", \"agent_name\", \"deployment_type\", \"namespace\", \"deployment\", \"service\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"replicas\", \"available_replicas\"}`\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Types\n\n| Exception | Source | Scenario |\n|-----------|--------|----------|\n| `ValueError` | Providers/Runtime | Missing required configuration fields |\n| `RuntimeError` | Providers | Kubernetes API failures, deployment failures |\n| `TimeoutError` | KubernetesProvider | Deployment readiness timeout exceeded |\n| `kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException` | K8s SDK | API-level errors (404, 409, etc.) |\n\n### Error Patterns\n\n#### Kubernetes API Errors\n\n```python\ntry:\n    result = api.create_namespaced_custom_object(...)\nexcept kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n    if e.status == 409:\n        # Resource exists - patch instead\n        result = api.patch_namespaced_custom_object(...)\n    elif e.status == 404 and \"AgentRuntime\" in str(e):\n        raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Install Volcano AgentCube CRDs\")\n    else:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime CR: {e}\")\n```\n\n#### Namespace Not Found\n\n```python\ntry:\n    core_api.read_namespace(name=namespace)\nexcept kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n    if e.status == 404:\n        core_api.create_namespace(body=namespace_body)\n    else:\n        raise\n```\n\n#### Delete Operations\n\n```python\ntry:\n    api.delete_namespaced_deployment(...)\n    deleted = True\nexcept kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException:\n    deleted = False  # Already deleted or not found - ignore\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### KubernetesProvider Tests\n\n| Test Class | Test Cases |\n|------------|------------|\n| `TestKubernetesProviderInit` | `test_init_default_namespace`, `test_init_custom_namespace`, `test_init_verbose` |\n| `TestSanitizeName` | `test_sanitize_name_lowercase`, `test_sanitize_name_replace_non_alphanumeric`, `test_sanitize_name_truncate_to_63_chars`, `test_sanitize_name_strip_dashes`, `test_sanitize_name_empty_string`, `test_sanitize_name_all_special_chars` |\n| `TestEnsureNamespace` | `test_ensure_namespace_exists`, `test_ensure_namespace_creates_if_not_exists` |\n| `TestCreateDeployment` | `test_create_deployment_basic`, `test_create_deployment_with_env_vars`, `test_create_deployment_with_entrypoint` |\n| `TestCreateService` | `test_create_service_basic`, `test_create_service_with_node_port`, `test_create_service_patch_if_exists` |\n| `TestWaitForDeploymentReady` | `test_wait_for_deployment_ready_success`, `test_wait_for_deployment_ready_timeout` |\n| `TestDeployAgent` | `test_deploy_agent_success` |\n| `TestGetAgentStatus` | `test_get_agent_status_success` |\n| `TestDeleteAgent` | `test_delete_agent_success` |\n| `TestNodePortValidation` | `test_node_port_min_boundary`, `test_node_port_max_boundary`, `test_default_timeout`, `test_poll_interval` |\n\n#### AgentCubeProvider Tests\n\n| Test Class | Test Cases |\n|------------|------------|\n| `TestAgentCubeProviderInit` | `test_init_default_namespace`, `test_init_custom_namespace`, `test_init_verbose`, `test_init_with_kubeconfig` |\n| `TestConstants` | `test_cr_group`, `test_cr_version`, `test_cr_plural`, `test_session_timeout`, `test_max_session_duration`, `test_default_secret` |\n| `TestSanitizeName` | Same pattern as KubernetesProvider |\n| `TestEnsureNamespace` | Same pattern as KubernetesProvider |\n| `TestDeployAgentRuntime` | `test_deploy_agent_runtime_success`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_with_entrypoint`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_patch_existing`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_crd_not_found`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_with_env_vars` |\n| `TestGetAgentRuntime` | `test_get_agent_runtime_success`, `test_get_agent_runtime_not_found`, `test_get_agent_runtime_custom_namespace` |\n| `TestDeleteAgentRuntime` | `test_delete_agent_runtime_success`, `test_delete_agent_runtime_not_found` |\n| `TestReadinessProbe` | `test_readiness_probe_default_values`, `test_readiness_probe_custom_values` |\n| `TestImagePullSecrets` | `test_image_pull_secrets_default` |\n\n### Test Patterns\n\nAll tests use `unittest.mock` to mock Kubernetes API calls:\n\n```python\ndef test_example(self) -> None:\n    with patch(\"kubernetes.config.load_kube_config\"):\n        mock_custom_api = MagicMock()\n        mock_custom_api.create_namespaced_custom_object.return_value = {\"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test\"}}\n        \n        with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\", return_value=mock_custom_api):\n            with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\"):\n                provider = AgentCubeProvider()\n                provider._custom_api = mock_custom_api\n                # Test logic here\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nIntegration tests require:\n- Running Kubernetes cluster (or kind/minikube)\n- Volcano AgentCube CRDs installed for AgentCubeProvider tests\n- Valid kubeconfig or incluster config\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider (342 lines)\n│   │   ├── agentcube_provider.py    # AgentCubeProvider (190 lines)\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py      # Metadata management\n│   │   └── docker_service.py        # Docker operations\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py       # PublishRuntime (271 lines)\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py        # InvokeRuntime (117 lines)\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py        # StatusRuntime (157 lines)\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py          # PackRuntime\n│   │   └── build_runtime.py         # BuildRuntime\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── pack_models.py           # MetadataOptions\n│   └── cli/\n│       ├── __init__.py\n│       └── main.py                   # Typer CLI commands\n├── tests/\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── test_k8s_provider.py         # KubernetesProvider unit tests (373 lines)\n│   ├── test_agentcube_provider.py   # AgentCubeProvider unit tests (446 lines)\n│   ├── test_publish_runtime.py\n│   ├── test_invoke_runtime.py\n│   ├── test_status_runtime.py\n│   └── ...\n├── examples/\n│   ├── hello-agent/\n│   │   └── main.py\n│   └── math-agent/\n│   │   └── main.py\n└── pyproject.toml\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes Python SDK (AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api, CustomObjectsApi) |\n| `httpx` | >=0.24.0 | Async HTTP client for invoke operations |\n| `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata validation (AgentMetadata) |\n| `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n| `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Rich console output |\n\n### Optional Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Testing framework |\n| `pytest-asyncio` | >=0.21.0 | Async test support |\n| `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mock fixtures |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Constants\n\n#### KubernetesProvider\n```python\nNODE_PORT_MIN = 30000     # Per Kubernetes spec\nNODE_PORT_MAX = 32767     # Per Kubernetes spec\nDEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120     # Seconds to wait for deployment readiness\nPOLL_INTERVAL = 2         # Seconds between readiness checks\n```\n\n#### AgentCubeProvider\n```python\nCR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\nCR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\nCR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\nSESSION_TIMEOUT = \"15m\"           # Default session timeout\nMAX_SESSION_DURATION = \"8h\"       # Maximum session duration\nDEFAULT_SECRET = \"default-secret\" # Default imagePullSecret\n```\n\n### Name Sanitization\n\nBoth providers use identical sanitization logic:\n1. Convert to lowercase\n2. Replace non-alphanumeric characters with `-`\n3. Collapse multiple dashes to single dash\n4. Strip leading/trailing dashes\n5. Truncate to 63 characters (Kubernetes name limit)\n6. Return `\"default\"` if result is empty\n\n### Lazy Provider Loading\n\nRuntime classes lazily import providers to avoid import errors when kubernetes package is not installed:\n\n```python\nif provider == \"k8s\":\n    from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n    self._k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\nelif provider == \"agentcube\":\n    from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n    self._agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\nelse:\n    raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n```\n\n### Endpoint Rewriting for AgentRuntime\n\nWhen invoking an AgentRuntime CR, the endpoint URL is rewritten:\n\n```python\n# Original endpoint from metadata\nendpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint\n\n# Rewritten for AgentRuntime CR\nsanitized_name = self._agentcube_provider._sanitize_name(metadata.agent_name)\nnamespace = k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\nbase_endpoint = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\nendpoint = f\"{base_endpoint}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{sanitized_name}/invocations/\"\n```\n\n### Session ID Management\n\nThe invoke flow manages session IDs bidirectionally:\n1. **Request**: Adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header if metadata contains `session_id`\n2. **Response**: Extracts `x-agentcube-session-id` from response headers and persists to metadata\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n- deployment/client-go.md — Kubernetes client-go library reference\n- python-sdk/spec.md — AgentCube Python SDK specification"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces